# Cursor Rules for Dekhe Trends Project

## Git Workflow Rules

### Before Committing
- Always check git status before committing
- Ensure all files are properly formatted
- Run linting if available
- Verify blog posts are included in commits

### Commit Messages
- Use clear, descriptive commit messages
- Format: "type: description"
- Examples:
  - "feat: add new blog post about trends"
  - "fix: resolve blog post indexing issue"
  - "docs: update deployment guide"

### Push Rules
- Always push to main/master branch
- Verify remote is set correctly: https://github.com/businessrg567-collab/DEKHE-TRENDS.git
- Use force push only when necessary (git push --force)
- After pushing, verify on GitHub that files are uploaded

### Deployment Checklist
Before pushing to GitHub, verify:
1. All blog posts are in server/blog-seed-data.ts
2. render.yaml is up to date
3. Environment variables are documented
4. Build script works (npm run build)
5. No sensitive data in commits (.env files ignored)

### Auto-Deploy Rules
- Repository: https://github.com/businessrg567-collab/DEKHE-TRENDS.git
- Default branch: main
- Auto-deploy is configured in Render
- Pushes to main trigger Render deployment automatically

### Blog Posts
- All blog posts must be in server/blog-seed-data.ts
- Each post should be 5000+ words
- SEO optimized with proper structure
- 20 blog posts total

### Environment Variables
Never commit:
- .env files
- API keys
- Database passwords
- Tokens

Always document in:
- .env.example
- README files

